div.p:
Now we turn around the motive in  m. 23 a little and take it in the right hand as it can be seen in the next beats in the
bass: but a third higher. An enthusiast of counterpoint will take the opportunity to note that both motives can be inverted back- and forward;
however it is not our intention here to play it that way on the keyboard and it is not feasible in all pieces.
